&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Junior Clinical Fellow in Plastic Surgery, based at Royal Preston Hospital initially for 12 month period with the possibility of a further 12 month extension on completion.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust forms one of the major acute Trusts in the North West with all of the usual specialties on site as well as being a Tertiary Centre for Lancashire and South Cumbria in the departments of Neurosciences, Oncology, Plastic Surgery and Burns and Renal Medicine. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Undergraduate medical student teaching has commenced in 2003 and the Trust has active and developing links with Universities of Manchester and Central Lancashire. Considerable opportunities exist for research and development, which are integral to teaching hospital status.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The unit consists of 10 Consultants, 1 Specialty Doctor, 5 Deanery Specialty Trainees, 6 Senior Clinical Fellows, 3 Deanery Core Surgery Trainees &amp; 3 Clinical Fellows (Junior level).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The full range of general adult and paediatric plastic surgery including microsurgery and burns is performed. Research is actively encouraged and considerable hands-on training is given. There are weekly teaching meetings and monthly audit meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries should be made with:- Mr Stuart McKirdy, Clinical Director Plastic Surgery. Email – jack.calvert@lthtr.nhs.uk. Phone number 01772 521327.&lt;/p&gt;
